The paper deals with problems related to graph connectivity and optimization, which are central topics in computer science. The use of linear programming and approximation algorithms suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-categories. The focus on graph theory and combinatorial optimization also suggests the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-categories. Finally, the use of iterative rounding and uncrossing techniques suggests the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category.
